 how past and current political and military leaders have responded to uncertain strategic and technological environments, and assesses the consequences of those strategies for their state's power and influence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aMilitary policyxHistory. 0aNational securityxHistoryxUnited States. 0aNational securityxHistory. 0aNational securityzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aStrategyxHistory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804777353zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804777353423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804777353.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles